  "prompt": "What is trading and how do I trade options?",
  "response": "Trading is the buying and selling of financial instruments like stocks, bonds, commodities, or derivatives with the goal of making a profit. Options trading specifically involves trading contracts that give you the right, but not the obligation, to buy or sell an underlying asset at a predetermined price.\n\nHere's a basic overview of options trading:\n\n1. Learn the basics:\n- Understand call and put options\n- Learn about strike prices and expiration dates\n- Study option pricing mechanisms\n\n2. Requirements:\n- Open a brokerage account with options trading approval\n- Have sufficient capital\n- Meet minimum requirements for options trading\n\n3. Basic options strategies:\n- Buying calls (betting price will go up)\n- Buying puts (betting price will go down)\n- Covered calls\n- Spreads\n\n4. Key steps to start:\n- Research and choose an underlying asset\n- Select an option contract\n- Determine your strategy\n- Calculate potential profit/loss\n- Execute trade through your broker\n\n5. Risk management:\n- Start small\n- Use stop-loss orders\n- Diversify\n- Only invest what you can afford to lose\n\n6. Continuous learning:\n- Take online courses\n- Read financial publications\n- Practice with paper trading\n- Stay updated on market trends\n\nRecommended: Consult a financial advisor and thoroughly educate yourself before trading.",
